Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on rock face showing four solidly pecked infilled figure of Nile river boat with bows to left, one above the other, ostrich, equid, bovid, unidentified quadrupeds and human figure. Lower leftmost boat has frond-type protuberances from stern. Ostrich pecked in outline stands to right, neck intersecting body of unidentified quadruped, upright and facing left, with another two, similar, to right. Above them is another, longer boat, bearing a equid (donkey?) and human figure sitting on something, same orientation To upper right is further curved boat, standing human figure with arms raised and schematic unidentified bovid-like animal. Below this is smallest boat figure with upright bow and stern. Small unidentified quadruped is at lower right. El-Kanais, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
